## Workday PRD Template

**Based on**: Interview Team Optimization Skill PRD (GA version)

**Format**: 11-page document structure with professional tone and formatting

**Key Characteristics**:
- Font: Standard (Calibri or similar)
- Tone: Professional, data-driven, strategic
- Length: Comprehensive (8-12 pages typical)
- British English spelling
- Page numbers: "X of Y" format at bottom

**CRITICAL - No Agentic Metadata**: Do NOT include pipeline IDs (GCC-E2E-NNN), HITL references, agent workflow steps, or internal tracking in the PRD header or Executive Summary. The PRD is a customer-facing professional document. Mission tracking belongs in MISSION_LOG.md only.

**Correct header format:**
```markdown
# [Feature Name] ([Release Version])
Product Requirements Document
[Month, Year]
```

**FORBIDDEN patterns in PRDs:**
- ❌ "**Pipeline:** GCC-E2E-028..."
- ❌ "HITL selection: ..."
- ❌ "PM framing applied per..."
- ❌ Any reference to agent numbers (@pmf-analyst, 105, @competitive-intel, 130, 315, 320, etc.) in body text
- ❌ "Mission GCC-E2E-NNN" in headings or prominent positions

**Acceptable internal references** (in body text only, when necessary for traceability):
- ✅ File paths to research: `research/GCC/thematic-analysis/2026-03-27-GCC-PMF-Analysis-GCC-E2E-025.md`
- ✅ "Source research: ..." with file path
- ✅ "PMF analysis (@pmf-analyst): ..." in Resources section only

